Glendenning's
first visit. There were his father and his
mother
,
Mary, Harry, and himself, living, actually living before
D 2
him. There were Mrs. Elton and Mr. Elton, Emmerson,
Glendenning, and poor little Seth.
Admirable! admirable! he murmured.
There was brought prominently and exquisitely out,
Fanny
Elton, her lovely self, and all the rest who had formed a
