to be seen, preparatory to a final return and a serious
business
career. He was, indeed, rather struck with the
earnestness
of his father's letter on this subject.
I wish you, thus it read, to bear continually in mind
that you are to acquaint yourself with the foundation of your
profession philosophically and historically, for which
purpose
you must by no means abandon your intention of
hearing
Savigny, and any other distinguished professor of
